x4freetext: The 3  MV PELLETRON accelerator of the
research laboratory for Nuclear Reactors at the Tokyo
Lithium target bombarded by 1.5 ns bunch
pulsed proton beam, repetition rate 4 MHz, proton
detector 15.2 cm diameter by 30.5 cm length was
centered in a hollow Compton-suppression Na-I(TL)
detector 33.0 cm outer diameter and  35.6 cm length
Li-6 glass detector for neutron flux monito-
ring. 5 mm diameter * 5 mm length 6-Li detector was
used for 15-100 KeV region, and 102 mm diameter *
6.4 mm length detector was used for 550 KeV.
Zirconium samples, monitor gold sample and
without any sample measurements were performed
.A gold sample was used as a standard, metallic,

.The correction for the neutron self-shielding and
multiple-scattering in the sample was made by Monte-
Carlo method. Other corrections were made for the
gamma-ray scattering and absorption in the sample
